The paper deals with group testing, which is a well-studied problem in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The introduction of hybrid items and the resulting increase in the number of possible models suggests a focus on machine learning and statistical modeling (cs.LG). The potential application in neuroscience (cs.NE) is explicitly mentioned in the abstract, and the use of group testing for classification is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
